We will consider several variables from the AddHealth data set. Looking in the code book for H1SU1 suggest responses of 6, 8, and 9 should be recoded to NA.

library(PDS)
xtabs(~H1SU1, data = AddHealth)
H1SU1
   0    1    6    8    9 
5614  821   46   22    1 
AddHealth$H1SU1[AddHealth$H1SU1==6 | AddHealth$H1SU1==8 | AddHealth$H1SU1==9] <- NA
xtabs(~H1SU1, data = AddHealth)
H1SU1
   0    1    6    8    9 
5614  821    0    0    0 
AddHealth$H1SU1 <- factor(AddHealth$H1SU1, labels = c("No", "Yes"))[, drop = TRUE]
xtabs(~H1SU1, data = AddHealth)
H1SU1
  No  Yes 
5614  821

Question H1SU2 asks the 821 repondents from H1SU1 “how many times did you attempt suicide?” Responses of 6, 7, and 8 should be recoded to NA.

xtabs(~H1SU2, data = AddHealth)
H1SU2
   0    1    2    3    4    6    7    8 
 587  131   64   10   25    3 5683    1 
AddHealth$H1SU2[AddHealth$H1SU2==6 | AddHealth$H1SU2==7 | AddHealth$H1SU2==8] <- NA
xtabs(~H1SU2, data = AddHealth)
H1SU2
  0   1   2   3   4   6   7   8 
587 131  64  10  25   0   0   0 
AddHealth$H1SU2 <- factor(AddHealth$H1SU2)[, drop = TRUE]

ggplot(data = AddHealth, aes(x = H1SU2)) +

ggplot(data = na.omit(AddHealth[ , "H1SU2", drop = FALSE]), aes(x = H1SU2)) +

  labs(x = "How many times did you actually attempt suicide?") +
  theme_bw()

Question H1SU3 asks of the 230 that attempted suicide if they had to be treated by either a nurse or doctor. The response of 7 should be recoded to NA.

AddHealth$H1SU3[AddHealth$H1SU3 == 7] <- NA
AddHealth$H1SU3 <- factor(AddHealth$H1SU3, labels = c("No", "Yes"))[, drop = TRUE]
